{"ID":270347, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"347\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs346.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs348.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 347<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">small degree<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> to another, and from a small capacity to a great one;<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> from grace to grace,<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> from\n  exaltation to exaltation,<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> until you attain to the resurrection of the dead,<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> and are able to dwell in\n  everlasting burnings,<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> and to sit in glory,<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> as do those who sit enthroned<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> in everlasting power.<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> And\n  I want you to know that God, in the last days, while certain individuals are proclaiming his name,<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span>\n  is not trifling<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> with you or me.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">The Righteous to Dwell in Everlasting Burnings<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">These are the first principles of consolation.<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> How consoling to the mourners<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> when they are\n  called to part with a husband, wife, father, mother, child, or dear relative, to know that, although the\n  earthly tabernacle is laid down and dissolved,<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> they shall rise again<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> to dwell in everlasting\n  burnings<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> in immortal glory,<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> not to sorrow, suffer, or die any more;<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> but they shall be heirs of God\n  and joint heirs with Jesus Christ.<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> What is it? To inherit the same power, the same glory<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> and the\n  same exaltation,<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span> until you arrive at the station of a God,<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span> and ascend the throne of eternal power,<span class=\"footRef\">23<\/span>\n  the same as those who have gone before.<span class=\"footRef\">24<\/span> What did Jesus do? Why; I do the things I saw my Father\n  do<span class=\"footRef\">25<\/span> when worlds come rolling into existence. My Father worked out his kingdom with fear and\n  trembling,<span class=\"footRef\">26<\/span> and I must do the same; and when I get my kingdom, I shall present it to my Father,<span class=\"footRef\">27<\/span>\n  so that he may obtain kingdom<span class=\"footRef\">28<\/span> upon kingdom,<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111391\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111391)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111391)\">Jacob 4:2<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112416\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112416)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112416)\">Hel. 3:22<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109642\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109642)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109642)\">2 Cor. 3:18<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115015\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115015)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115015)\">D&amp;C 93:13<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116373\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116373)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116373)\">D&amp;C 132:19,22-23<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109873\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109873)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109873)\">Philip. 3:11<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">6. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107136\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107136)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107136)\">Isa. 33:14<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">7. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108358\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108358)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108358)\">Mark 10:37<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">8. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116407\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116407)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116407)\">D&amp;C 132:29<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">9. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112196\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112196)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112196)\">Alma 36:29<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">10. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106209\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106209)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106209)\">Ex. 33:19<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106211\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106211)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106211)\">Ex. 34:5<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115675\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115675)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115675)\">D&amp;C 112:19<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">11. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113562\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113562)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113562)\">D&amp;C 32:5<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">12. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109671\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109671)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109671)\">2 Cor. 7:7<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">13. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107810\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107810)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107810)\">Matt. 5:4<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108761\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108761)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108761)\">John 11:19<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">14. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106601\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106601)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106601)\">Job 19:26-27<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109649\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109649)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109649)\">2 Cor. 5:1<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">15. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108136\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108136)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108136)\">Matt. 20:19<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108762\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108762)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108762)\">John 11:23<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112002\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112002)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112002)\">Alma 19:8<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112130\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112130)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112130)\">Alma 33:22<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114828\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114828)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114828)\">D&amp;C 88:27<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">16. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107137\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107137)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107137)\">Isa. 33:14<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">17. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116847\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116847)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116847)\">Moses 6:59,61<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">18. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107381\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107381)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107381)\">Jer. 31:12<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108565\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108565)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108565)\">Luke 20:36<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110871\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110871)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110871)\">Rev. 21:4<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">19. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109298\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109298)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109298)\">Rom. 8:17<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">20. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108878\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108878)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108878)\">John 17:22<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114833\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114833)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114833)\">D&amp;C 88:29<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115024\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115024)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115024)\">D&amp;C 93:22<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">21. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108794\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108794)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108794)\">John 14:2-3<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">22. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116381\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116381)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116381)\">D&amp;C 132:20<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">23. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109234\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109234)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109234)\">Rom. 1:20<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113834\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113834)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113834)\">D&amp;C 45:8<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116691\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116691)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116691)\">D&amp;C 138:51<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">24. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116408\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116408)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116408)\">D&amp;C 132:29-32<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">25. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108673\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108673)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108673)\">John 5:19-20<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">26. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109868\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109868)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109868)\">Philip. 2:12<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112834\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112834)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112834)\">Morm. 9:27<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">27. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114494\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114494)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114494)\">D&amp;C 76:107<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">28. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114473\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114473)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114473)\">D&amp;C 76:79<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n  <\/div>\n  <div class=\"textFootnotes\">\n    \n      <p class=\"cont\">at exceptional glorification of his body is a pious heresy&mdash;a heresy which misses the truth lying open to our eyes. His humanity is to be recognised as real and ordinary and thorough and complete:\n        not in middle life alone,\n        but at birth, and at death and after death. Whatever happened to him may happen to any one of us, provided we attain the appropriate altitude:\n        an altitude which, whether within our individual reach or not, is assuredly within reach of humanity. That is what he urged again and again. &ldquo;Be born again.&rdquo; &ldquo;Be ye perfect.&rdquo; &ldquo;Ye are the sons of God.&rdquo; &ldquo;My Father and your Father, my God and your God.&rdquo;<\/p>\n        <p class=\"std\">The <i>un<\/i>uniqueness of the ordinary humanity of Christ is the first and patent truth, masked only by well-meaning and reverent superstition. But the second truth is greater than that&mdash;without it the first would be meaningless and useless,&mdash;if man alone, what gain have we? The world is full of men. What the world wants is a God. Behold the God!&mdash;[That is, the God, Jesus Christ.]<\/p>\n      <p class=\"std\">The Divinity of Jesus is the truth which now requires to be re-perceived to be illumined afresh by new knowledge, to be cleansed and revivified by the wholesome flood of scepticism which has poured over it; it can be freed now from all trace of grovelling superstition, and can be recognised freely and enthusiastically: the Divinity of Jesus, and [the divinity] of all other noble and saintly souls, in so far as they too have been inflamed by a spark of Deity&mdash;in so far as they too can be recognised as manifestations of the Divine.&mdash;Notes by Elder B. H. Roberts.<\/p>\n    \n  <\/div>\n<\/div>"}